title: Baba Mountain
snippet: 2601m mountain overlooking Bitola, home to Pelister peak & forested slopes with hiking trails.
extensions/2: 2601m mountain overlooking Bitola, home to Pelister peak & forested slopes with hiking trails.
description: ОписБаба — гірський масив між Македонією та Грецією. Також відомий за назвою найвищої вершини Пелістер чи Перістері, що має висоту 2601 м. Знаходиться неподалік міста Бітола. За висотою гора є третьою у Македонії та п'ятнадцятою у Греції.

title: Plačkovica
description:
DescriptionPlačkovica is a mountain located the eastern part of North Macedonia, it extends between the cities of Radoviš, and Vinica.
The highest peak is Lisec at 1,754 m, the length of main valley slopes of the peak Lisec is 34 km. The valley of Zrnovska river splits the mountain in two, eastern and western parts.

title: Mt Korab
snippet: 7 climbing routes reach this 2,751-m. peak, including one that incorporates a gondola ride.
extensions/2: 7 climbing routes reach this 2,751-m. peak, including one that incorporates a gondola ride.
description: DescriptionMount Korab is the highest peak of the eponymous mountain range and the fourth highest mountain entirely located in the Balkan Peninsula, standing at 2,764 metres.

title: Galičica
snippet: Snow-capped with flower-covered slopes, this mountain offers river views from its peaks.
extensions/2: Snow-capped with flower-covered slopes, this mountain offers river views from its peaks.
description: DescriptionGaličica is a mountain situated across the border between North Macedonia and Albania. There is a national park on the North Macedonian side of the mountain, situated between the two biggest lakes in the republic: Lake Ohrid and Lake Prespa. It stretches over an area of 227 square kilometres.

title: Šar Mountains
snippet: Beyond its sweeping views & soaring peaks, this scenic mountain range features a national park.
extensions/2: Beyond its sweeping views & soaring peaks, this scenic mountain range features a national park.
description: ОписШар-Планина або Шар-Даг — гірський хребет на Балканському півострові. Основна частина знаходиться на території Північної Македонії і Косово і Метохії, невелика частина — в Албанії. Простягається з північного сходу на південний захід на 75 км. Найвищі піки — Титов-Врх і Турчин.

title: Dešat
description: DescriptionDešat or Deshat is a mountain on the border between Albania and North Macedonia. The mountain is characterised by its steep peaks: Mal and Golem Krčin and Velivar. The highest peak on the mountain, Velivar, 2,375 m above the sea level. Other significant peaks are: Deli Senica, and Suva Bara.

title: Kožuf
description: DescriptionKožuf mountain or Tzena / Zona is a mountain situated in the southern part of North Macedonia and northern part of Greece.

title: Ograzhden
description: DescriptionOgrazhden is a mountain shared by southeastern North Macedonia and southwestern Bulgaria, part of the Belasitsa-Osogovo group. It is located north of Belasitsa, northeast of the Macedonian town of Strumitsa and northwest of the Bulgarian town of Petrich.

title: Skopska Crna Gora
description: DescriptionSkopska Crna Gora, often called and only as Crna Gora, Albanian: Malet e Karadakut, is a mountain range largely in Macedonia, with smaller part in Kosovo. It lies between the cities of Kaçanik and Skopje. The highest peak is Ramno in Macedonia. The largest town on the mountain is Kučevište in North Macedonia.

title: Vodno
snippet: 1,066-m. mountain featuring hiking, churches, the Millennium Cross, the Prskalo waterfall & more.
extensions/2: 1,066-m. mountain featuring hiking, churches, the Millennium Cross, the Prskalo waterfall & more.
description: DescriptionVodno is a mountain in North Macedonia. It is located in the northern part of the country, to the southwest of the capital city Skopje. The highest point of the mountain is at Krstovar peak, on 1066 meters and the submontane is on 337 meters.

title: Osogovo
snippet: Picturesque, 2252-m. peak known for all-season recreation like skiing & hiking alongside wildlife.
extensions/2: Picturesque, 2252-m. peak known for all-season recreation like skiing & hiking alongside wildlife.
description: DescriptionOsogovo or Osogovska Planina is a mountain and ski resort between the southwestern part of Bulgaria and the northeastern part of North Macedonia.

title: Kozjak
description: DescriptionKozjak is a mountain situated on the border between North Macedonia and Serbia. It is situated north-east from Kumanovo. The tallest peak of Kozjak is Virovi at 1284 meters. The region is also known as Kozjačija.

title: Belasica
snippet: Picturesque mountain range with a lake, waterfalls, Mediterranean climate & watchtower ruins.
extensions/2: Picturesque mountain range with a lake, waterfalls, Mediterranean climate & watchtower ruins.
description: DescriptionBelasica, Belles or Kerkini, is a mountain range in the region of Macedonia in Southeastern Europe, shared by northeastern Greece, southeastern North Macedonia and southwestern Bulgaria.

title: Jablanica Mountain
description:
DescriptionJablanica is a mountain range in Southern and Southeastern Europe, stretching north-south direction across the border of Albania and North Macedonia.
The long mountain ridge is higher than 2,000 m for approximately 50 km, while the highest part, located in its very center, is Black Stone at 2,257 m high.

title: Dobra Voda
description: DescriptionDobra Voda is a mountain near the town of Kičevo in North Macedonia. It is the highest peak of the Celoica mountain range, at 2062 metres above the sea level. Due to tectonic movements, the height of this peak and surrounding mountains continues to rise.

title: Titov Vrv
description: DescriptionTitov Vrv is the highest peak in the Šar Mountains at 2,748 m. It is located about 13 mi northwest of the Macedonian city of Tetovo, near the border with Kosovo. The summit was named after former Yugoslav communist leader Josip Broz Tito. Its original name was Голем Турчин/Golem Turčin.

title: Maleshevo
description: DescriptionThe Maleshevo Mountain or Maleševo Mountain, is situated in southwestern Bulgaria and eastern North Macedonia. It is the third of the five mountains of the Osogovo-Belasitsa mountain group, known also as the Western Border Mountains. The highest point is Ilyov Vrah.
